<P>BY A CITIZEN OF PHILADELPHIA.</P>
<Q><L>Who taught the rapid winds to fly &s;o fa&s;t,</L>
<L>Or &s;hakes the centre with his ea&s;tern bla&s;t?</L>
<L>Who from the &s;kies can a whole deluge pour?</L>
<L>Who &s;trikes through Nature with the &s;olemn roar</L>
<L>Of dreadful thunder, points it where to fall,</L>
<L>And in fierce lightning wraps the flying ball?</L>
<BIBL>YOUNG.</BIBL></Q>
