<L>Here rai&s;e the noble&s;t trophies of renown,</L>
<L>Far from the zealot's rage, the monarch's frown?</L>
<L>To &s;ave a world from proud, imperious Spain,</L>
<L>(Once <HI>Europe</HI>'s dread, and mi&s;tre&s;s of the main)</L>
<L N="345"> By rage oppre&s;s'd, by avarice defpoil'd,</L>
<L>The patriot coun&s;el'd, and the hero toil'd.</L>
<L>But ah! &s;ad victim of tyrannic pride,</L>
<L>The &s;age, the hero, and the patriot died!</L>
<L>For you, the tender objects of his care,</L>
<L N="350"> His late&s;t &s;igh he breath'd, his late&s;t prayer;</L>
<L>And fondly hop'd, beyond th' Atlantic main</L>
<L>Commerce, and Arts, and Liberty might reign.</L>
<L>And has he vainly hop'd?&mdash;U<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> taught to yield</L>
<L>In the dire conflict of the well-fought field,</L>
<L N="355"> Scorning to Tyranny to bow the knee,</L>
<L>Ye toil'd, ye fought, ye <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">quer'd, and were free.</L>
<L>But &s;hall the noble &s;trife be incomplete?</L>
<L>Fair Virtue's hopes &s;hall Luxury defeat?</L>
<L>Have heroes bled, &s;hall patriots plan in vain,</L>
<L N="360"> And your &s;hort page of hi&s;tory fury &s;tain?</L>
<PB N="122" REF="021081_0118_0FB23B1ED2454EA0">
<L>With vain ideas of fal&s;e grandeur curs'd,</L>
<L>The plan of Wi&s;dom wildly ye revers'd,</L>
<L>And, to curs'd luxury unwi&s;ely prone,</L>
<L>Rewarded ev'ry arti&s;t but your own.</L>
<L N="365"> For foreign arts your bo&s;oms madly glow;</L>
<L>For foreign wants ye real joys forego;</L>
<L>And, whil&s;t ye thus di&s;grace the noble&s;t cau&s;e,</L>
<L>Rea&s;on exclaims "beware of foreign laws."</L>
<L>Though wealth in Europe's co&s;tly fa&s;hions flaunt,</L>
<L N="370"> Shall Indu&s;try for glitt'ring trifles pant?</L>
<L>Though maddening plea&s;ures charm the haughty train,</L>
<L>The vile <HI>Circean</HI> bowl &s;hall <HI>Labour</HI> drain?</L>
<L>If city <HI>Mira</HI> mimics foreign aris,</L>
<L>And in imported pride and finery glares,</L>
<L N="375"> Already charming in her &s;hepherd's eye,</L>
<L>Shall rural <HI>Phyllis</HI> with the rainbow vie?</L>
<L>Too weak the load of luxury to bear,</L>
<L>For foreign foes new triumphs ye prepare;</L>
<L>And, whil&s;t the land but half her ble&s;&s;ings reaps,</L>
<L N="380"> Each virtue &s;ickens, and <HI>Religion</HI> weeps.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Let toil, let arts henceforth demand your care,</L>
<L>And &s;hun alike mad triumph, and de&s;pair.</L>
<L>Though a wild &s;cene of horror &s;pread around,</L>
<L>How light your woes in rea&s;on's &s;cale are found,</L>
<L N="385"> With tho&s;e compar'd, which &s;hake <HI>Sicilia's</HI> i&s;le;</L>
<L>Or the fell offspring of di&s;a&s;trous <HI>Nile?</HI></L>
<L>In <HI>Egypt</HI>'s fens by <HI>heat</HI> and <HI>vapour</HI> nurs'd,</L>
<L>Death-breathing <HI>pe&s;tilence,</HI> by Nature curs'd,</L>
<L>Re&s;olves o'er di&s;tant lands to &s;pread his &s;way,</L>
<L N="390"> And in dire triumph meditates his prey,</L>
<L><HI>Byzantium,</HI> thee!&mdash;Pale <HI>Sickne&s;s,</HI> trembling <HI>Fear,</HI></L>
<L>And agonizing <HI>Pain,</HI> and wild <HI>De&s;pair,</HI></L>
<L>Mark his dire route&mdash;within thy horrid gates,</L>
<L><HI>Squalor,</HI> with <HI>Apathy,</HI> his entrance waits.</L>
<PB N="123" REF="021081_0119_0FB23B2048021838">
<L N="395"> Ha&s;tening with gha&s;tly &s;mile through groaning &s;treets,</L>
<L>With love fraternal <HI>De&s;poti&s;m</HI> he greets;</L>
<L>Awes by &s;uperior rage the &s;ervile train,</L>
<L>A&s;&s;erts the throne, and takes his turn to reigh.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Ye free! how vain tho&s;e evils to repeat,</L>
<L N="400"> Which rack the foreign poor, or awe the great,</L>
<L>Since truer joys are yours, and fewer woes,</L>
<L>On <HI>Liberty</HI> and <HI>Toil</HI> your hopes repo&s;e;</L>
<L>Till di&s;tant lands &s;hall emulate your fame,</L>
<L>And in triumphant accents <HI>Truth</HI> exclaim,</L>
<L N="405"> Behold the men, of <HI>Freedom</HI>'s joys po&s;&s;e&s;s'd,</L>
<L>By <HI>Labour</HI> wealthy, and by <HI>Virtue</HI> ble&s;s'd."</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>He &s;poke, and, plunging &s;eeks his wave-&s;coop'd dome;</L>
<L>O'er his huge frame the clo&s;ing billows foam.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>THE END</TRAILER>
